1
00:00:07,740 --> 00:00:08,840
We'll always be

2
00:00:09,260 --> 00:00:11,240
best friends, just like we've always been.

3
00:00:12,520 --> 00:00:13,670
That's for the best.

4
00:00:15,940 --> 00:00:17,040
Because if I see you,

5
00:00:18,220 --> 00:00:20,400
I won't be able to hide
how much I love you.

6
00:00:27,900 --> 00:00:29,380
I'm just too in love with you.

7
00:00:32,700 --> 00:00:34,500
- (I want to see you.)
- (I want to see you.)

8
00:00:41,460 --> 00:00:42,460
Minato.

9
00:00:46,820 --> 00:00:47,820
Wataru.

10
00:01:35,900 --> 00:01:37,900
"Countdown To Yes"

11
00:01:42,500 --> 00:01:45,700
(Final Episode)

12
00:01:45,730 --> 00:01:46,730
Long time no see.

13
00:01:48,840 --> 00:01:49,840
Long time no see.

14
00:01:51,110 --> 00:01:52,110
So...

15
00:01:53,346 --> 00:01:54,546
why did we come to the beach?

16
00:01:57,220 --> 00:01:58,220
Close your eyes.

17
00:01:58,520 --> 00:01:59,720
Wait, what for?

18
00:01:59,730 --> 00:02:00,730
Just trust me.

19
00:02:00,810 --> 00:02:01,810
No way.

20
00:02:02,350 --> 00:02:03,450
How about this?

21
00:02:03,960 --> 00:02:06,330
Whoa, whoa, hold on! That's dangerous!

22
00:02:06,880 --> 00:02:07,880
How does it feel?

23
00:02:10,110 --> 00:02:11,670
When your back is to the sea,

24
00:02:11,870 --> 00:02:13,350
doesn't it feel kind of unsettling?

25
00:02:16,020 --> 00:02:17,020
I guess.

26
00:02:17,400 --> 00:02:18,400
A little bit.

27
00:02:18,570 --> 00:02:20,280
It's kind of creepy.

28
00:02:20,870 --> 00:02:22,260
What if you do this?

29
00:02:26,890 --> 00:02:29,210
If you actually look at
it, it's not scary anymore.

30
00:02:29,250 --> 00:02:30,370
You don't have to be afraid.

31
00:02:31,610 --> 00:02:33,610
If you watch the height
and distance of the waves,

32
00:02:34,010 --> 00:02:35,500
you'll know they won't reach you.

33
00:02:39,700 --> 00:02:41,190
Wait, we're gonna get soaked!

34
00:02:43,430 --> 00:02:44,430
Sorry.

35
00:02:44,810 --> 00:02:46,970
I guess these waves are a bit too rough
for a metaphor.

36
00:02:47,430 --> 00:02:48,430
What metaphor?

37
00:02:50,090 --> 00:02:52,210
I just wanted to be honest with you.

38
00:02:56,490 --> 00:02:58,040
The things you're afraid of, Wataru...

39
00:02:58,600 --> 00:03:00,070
are they really that bad?

40
00:03:02,710 --> 00:03:05,050
Or are you just scared because
you refuse to look at them?

41
00:03:12,500 --> 00:03:14,220
I love you, Wataru.

42
00:03:17,850 --> 00:03:20,060
And I don't think that's
ever going to change.

43
00:03:21,940 --> 00:03:23,820
I never want to be apart from you again.

44
00:03:25,610 --> 00:03:27,870
Whether we're happy or sad,
I want to be there with you.

45
00:03:28,590 --> 00:03:30,350
I want to be by your side, watching you...

46
00:03:31,070 --> 00:03:33,510
and taking photos of you
from the best seat in the house.

47
00:03:37,050 --> 00:03:39,130
I want to capture every moment

48
00:03:39,600 --> 00:03:40,950
of how I feel when I'm with you.

49
00:03:44,080 --> 00:03:46,120
No matter how small or
insignificant the moment is,

50
00:03:47,030 --> 00:03:48,740
I want you to be the one by my side.

51
00:03:50,080 --> 00:03:51,080
So,

52
00:03:52,660 --> 00:03:53,660
I want to understand.

53
00:03:57,110 --> 00:03:58,090
At the very least, when it comes to you,

54
00:03:58,091 --> 00:03:59,171
I want to truly understand.

55
00:04:02,890 --> 00:04:04,570
How do you really feel about me?

56
00:04:05,723 --> 00:04:07,443
Why are you so afraid of romantic feelings?

57
00:04:11,390 --> 00:04:12,950
Face up to it.

58
00:04:14,400 --> 00:04:15,400
Tell me.

59
00:04:25,810 --> 00:04:26,810
Face up to it...

60
00:04:31,650 --> 00:04:32,650
I'm facing up to it.

61
00:04:33,370 --> 00:04:36,250
I was so scared that our time
as best friends would turn out to be a lie.

62
00:04:37,200 --> 00:04:38,360
All those happy times...

63
00:04:38,740 --> 00:04:40,630
those moments where
we just "got" each other...

64
00:04:41,280 --> 00:04:43,590
If that was all just because
of romantic feelings...

65
00:04:43,980 --> 00:04:44,980
I don't know...

66
00:04:45,150 --> 00:04:50,489
It's like, was our friendship
just one big lie?

67
00:04:50,490 --> 00:04:52,270
- That's not...
- No.

68
00:04:52,390 --> 00:04:53,430
It's not like that at all.

69
00:04:54,910 --> 00:04:56,230
The reason those times were happy

70
00:04:56,500 --> 00:04:57,910
was because it was you and me.

71
00:04:58,856 --> 00:05:01,105
I was happy because I was with you, Minato.

72
00:05:01,130 --> 00:05:02,469
It was only because it was you.

73
00:05:02,470 --> 00:05:03,789
It had nothing to do with
some "romance filter."

74
00:05:03,790 --> 00:05:04,790
So...

75
00:05:08,560 --> 00:05:10,789
our time as best friends was never a lie.

76
00:05:10,790 --> 00:05:11,790
I know.

77
00:05:19,210 --> 00:05:21,220
You called it a romance filter.

78
00:05:22,490 --> 00:05:23,390
But even with a filter,

79
00:05:23,391 --> 00:05:25,191
you can't capture
something that isn't there.

80
00:05:27,010 --> 00:05:32,900
Filters exist to make you love
what's in front of you even more.

81
00:05:33,390 --> 00:05:35,270
To make everything feel more precious.

82
00:05:36,350 --> 00:05:38,270
Wataru, weren't you
the one who told me that?

83
00:05:46,680 --> 00:05:47,680
We are best friends,

84
00:05:48,600 --> 00:05:49,400
and we love each other.

85
00:05:49,401 --> 00:05:50,721
Neither of those things is a lie.

86
00:06:00,530 --> 00:06:04,610
So I don't have to be two different people?

87
00:06:06,360 --> 00:06:07,460
Two people?

88
00:06:08,100 --> 00:06:09,890
Yeah, like I'm split.

89
00:06:11,740 --> 00:06:12,940
Between being your best friend

90
00:06:13,150 --> 00:06:14,250
and being your lover.

91
00:06:15,630 --> 00:06:16,630
No.

92
00:06:17,530 --> 00:06:18,830
You just need to be Wataru.

93
00:06:21,820 --> 00:06:22,820
I see.

94
00:06:23,250 --> 00:06:24,250
That's a relief.

95
00:06:24,570 --> 00:06:25,930
I'm glad I can just be one person.

96
00:06:26,320 --> 00:06:28,200
People are supposed to
have many sides to them.

97
00:06:31,340 --> 00:06:32,340
Yeah.

98
00:06:43,642 --> 00:06:47,762
Actually... ever since
you asked me to move in,

99
00:06:48,630 --> 00:06:50,120
I've only been thinking about myself.

100
00:06:51,270 --> 00:06:53,190
I was so obsessed with
being your "best friend."

101
00:06:54,260 --> 00:06:55,940
And then we ended up apart.

102
00:06:56,930 --> 00:06:58,030
It was really hard for me.

103
00:07:00,370 --> 00:07:02,770
Hearing things about
you from other people...

104
00:07:03,470 --> 00:07:04,670
it made me feel so frustrated.

105
00:07:07,280 --> 00:07:08,960
Even your grandpa being in the hospital...

106
00:07:09,280 --> 00:07:10,960
I had to hear it from Shio-kun and my mom.

107
00:07:11,520 --> 00:07:13,030
I hated that so much.

108
00:07:14,370 --> 00:07:16,380
I ran into Shio-kun at the hospital.

109
00:07:17,800 --> 00:07:19,000
How's your grandpa doing?

110
00:07:19,940 --> 00:07:22,200
He's already home, just
taking it easy and resting.

111
00:07:23,860 --> 00:07:24,860
That's good.

112
00:07:25,830 --> 00:07:26,830
No, wait.

113
00:07:28,380 --> 00:07:29,649
I know it might be too late to say this,

114
00:07:29,650 --> 00:07:31,440
and I might have missed my chance,

115
00:07:32,090 --> 00:07:34,260
but... I'm so sorry.

116
00:07:41,330 --> 00:07:42,330
I...

117
00:07:43,910 --> 00:07:45,260
I love you, Minato.

118
00:07:53,600 --> 00:07:54,600
Are you mad?

119
00:07:57,580 --> 00:07:58,580
I'm just really happy.

120
00:08:02,590 --> 00:08:03,690
So, what do you want to do?

121
00:08:04,950 --> 00:08:05,950
I...

122
00:08:09,440 --> 00:08:12,080
I want to be with you.

123
00:08:17,560 --> 00:08:18,660
Every single day,

124
00:08:18,690 --> 00:08:19,850
I don't want to miss a thing.

125
00:08:27,940 --> 00:08:29,040
I'm so glad.

126
00:08:29,230 --> 00:08:30,230
We feel the same way.

127
00:08:31,730 --> 00:08:32,730
Yeah.

128
00:08:34,120 --> 00:08:35,120
Exactly the same.

129
00:08:35,900 --> 00:08:37,200
Everything.

130
00:08:42,790 --> 00:08:44,070
What about... kissing and stuff?

131
00:08:44,740 --> 00:08:46,730
If you're not ready, we don't have to.

132
00:08:47,940 --> 00:08:49,560
Just being with you is enough.

133
00:08:52,020 --> 00:08:53,020
Let's do it.

134
00:08:53,540 --> 00:08:54,540
Huh?

135
00:09:02,270 --> 00:09:03,870
I mean, this is the perfect time for it.

136
00:09:08,270 --> 00:09:09,940
People have many sides, right?

137
00:09:19,000 --> 00:09:20,000
Are you blushing?

138
00:09:21,310 --> 00:09:22,310
You caught me.

139
00:09:23,170 --> 00:09:24,489
So all those times you were being grumpy...

140
00:09:24,490 --> 00:09:25,610
was that just you being shy?

141
00:09:26,390 --> 00:09:27,390
Yeah.

142
00:09:28,320 --> 00:09:30,060
Oh my god, that's so cute.

143
00:09:31,060 --> 00:09:33,020
- Right?
- Don't just agree with me!

144
00:09:47,360 --> 00:09:48,360
Say it again.

145
00:09:51,400 --> 00:09:52,400
Wataru.

146
00:09:52,660 --> 00:09:53,660
Yeah?

147
00:09:55,010 --> 00:09:56,010
Will you...

148
00:09:57,160 --> 00:09:58,160
move in with me?

149
00:10:00,740 --> 00:10:01,740
Yeah.

150
00:10:02,290 --> 00:10:03,290
I'd love to.

151
00:10:09,400 --> 00:10:10,650
I am not blushing.

152
00:10:10,850 --> 00:10:12,050
You totally are.

153
00:10:12,120 --> 00:10:13,120
I said I'm not!

154
00:10:13,680 --> 00:10:16,400
- Liar, it's so obvious!
- Fine, then kiss me again.

155
00:10:22,740 --> 00:10:23,740
It's freezing.

156
00:10:24,100 --> 00:10:25,400
My feet are like ice.

157
00:10:25,890 --> 00:10:27,740
Well, you're the one
who wanted to come here.

158
00:10:28,340 --> 00:10:31,010
Couldn't you find a better
spot just to use that metaphor?

159
00:10:31,030 --> 00:10:33,050
- Like a cliff? That'd be dangerous.
- A cliff?

160
00:10:33,580 --> 00:10:35,430
When we celebrate our 20th anniversary,

161
00:10:35,570 --> 00:10:37,050
I'll make sure to pick a better spot.

162
00:10:37,570 --> 00:10:39,860
We don't need to
celebrate a 20th anniversary.

163
00:10:40,090 --> 00:10:41,090
Then what should we do?

164
00:10:41,770 --> 00:10:43,020
Let's just take photos.

165
00:10:43,470 --> 00:10:45,870
I'll make sure to capture every
single one of your wrinkles.

166
00:10:46,470 --> 00:10:47,250
Ah!

167
00:10:47,251 --> 00:10:49,499
Don't make such a great face
when I don't have my camera!

168
00:10:49,500 --> 00:10:50,800
Even if you say that...

169
00:10:55,960 --> 00:10:57,090
Oh, right.

170
00:10:59,940 --> 00:11:01,760
I got it developed, so I brought it.

171
00:11:02,600 --> 00:11:03,600
That photo I took before.

172
00:11:03,940 --> 00:11:04,940
Thanks.

173
00:11:06,070 --> 00:11:10,070
This is the best expression
I've ever seen on you.

174
00:11:10,390 --> 00:11:11,390
Look.

175
00:11:11,430 --> 00:11:12,430
Oh.

176
00:11:13,743 --> 00:11:15,390
I get it, you're embarrassed.

177
00:11:15,610 --> 00:11:17,840
- Okay, give it here.
- No way.

178
00:11:17,930 --> 00:11:20,600
- This is my masterpiece.
- Hey!

179
00:11:22,530 --> 00:11:24,160
This expression is seriously amazing.

180
00:11:24,190 --> 00:11:25,930
Hmm, where should I hang it?

181
00:11:26,500 --> 00:11:27,500
Ah.

182
00:11:27,610 --> 00:11:29,789
Then I'll find the best photo
I've taken of you...

183
00:11:29,790 --> 00:11:30,910
Hey! Don't look at them now!

184
00:11:37,430 --> 00:11:39,010
- Here you go.
- Thanks.

185
00:11:44,200 --> 00:11:45,760
Change can be a scary thing.

186
00:11:46,510 --> 00:11:47,510
But,

187
00:11:48,000 --> 00:11:50,420
the time we've spent
together won't just disappear.

188
00:11:53,650 --> 00:11:56,110
Minato is the only one who
can capture my best side.

189
00:11:57,080 --> 00:11:59,750
And I'm the only one who can capture his.

190
00:12:00,510 --> 00:12:01,510
My arm's gonna fall off.

191
00:12:02,360 --> 00:12:03,610
From now on, and forever,

192
00:12:04,030 --> 00:12:05,030
I hope it stays that way.

193
00:12:06,490 --> 00:12:08,210
Best friends and lovers.

194
00:12:09,390 --> 00:12:11,030
Lovers and best friends.

195
00:12:12,080 --> 00:12:13,370
The one and only.

196
00:12:14,260 --> 00:12:15,260
My

197
00:12:16,110 --> 00:12:17,620
Irreplaceable person.

198
00:12:20,210 --> 00:12:21,310
Forever.

199
00:12:22,100 --> 00:12:23,500
The person I want to be with.

200
00:12:37,430 --> 00:12:38,430
Wataru.

201
00:12:38,530 --> 00:12:40,570
(November 3, 2025)
- Oh no, this is bad. - Hmm?

202
00:12:40,800 --> 00:12:41,826
(Rental Application (Individual))
You brought it, right? Is everything okay?

203
00:12:41,850 --> 00:12:42,850
Huh?

204
00:12:42,860 --> 00:12:43,530
What's wrong?

205
00:12:43,830 --> 00:12:44,959
Wait! All the documents...

206
00:12:44,960 --> 00:12:46,609
Did you bring them? All of them?

207
00:12:46,610 --> 00:12:47,320
I have them.

208
00:12:47,321 --> 00:12:48,700
- It's fine.
- Are you sure?

209
00:12:49,100 --> 00:12:51,310
Yeah, we're good.

210
00:12:51,830 --> 00:12:54,170
I just received the photo of your ID.

211
00:12:54,230 --> 00:12:56,270
The screening results
should be out by next Monday.

212
00:12:56,610 --> 00:12:58,760
But for you two, it shouldn't be a problem.

213
00:12:59,380 --> 00:13:00,580
Thanks for everything.

214
00:13:01,730 --> 00:13:02,770
Congratulations, you guys.

215
00:13:03,010 --> 00:13:04,010
Seriously.

216
00:13:07,200 --> 00:13:08,200
Oh, wait, sorry.

217
00:13:08,390 --> 00:13:09,390
I mean...

218
00:13:09,670 --> 00:13:10,990
Now that the place is official...

219
00:13:11,110 --> 00:13:12,700
I just wanted to say congratulations.

220
00:13:14,820 --> 00:13:16,660
I'm just really happy for you both.

221
00:13:17,520 --> 00:13:19,760
It's actually kind of making me emotional.

222
00:13:25,160 --> 00:13:26,160
Thanks.

223
00:13:26,540 --> 00:13:27,540
Huh?

224
00:13:28,530 --> 00:13:29,530
Thank you.

225
00:13:31,640 --> 00:13:32,640
Yeah.

226
00:13:32,670 --> 00:13:33,670
Congratulations.

227
00:13:35,100 --> 00:13:36,380
Shio-kun, you should say it too.

228
00:13:36,670 --> 00:13:37,670
And the baby.

229
00:13:38,800 --> 00:13:39,860
Oh, do you want to see?

230
00:13:39,910 --> 00:13:40,910
The ultrasound photo.

231
00:13:40,950 --> 00:13:42,830
Their face is absolutely adorable.

232
00:13:43,630 --> 00:13:45,479
- Wait, can you even tell yet?
- No, probably not.

233
00:13:45,480 --> 00:13:47,530
Yes, you can! Look, look right here.

234
00:13:48,320 --> 00:13:49,560
Look at this.

235
00:13:56,600 --> 00:13:58,500
(November 16, 2025)

236
00:13:58,590 --> 00:13:59,590
Oh, did you get it?

237
00:14:00,740 --> 00:14:02,100
Look at the lens. Are you looking?

238
00:14:03,400 --> 00:14:04,400
Okay.

239
00:14:04,940 --> 00:14:06,220
How is it?

240
00:14:06,340 --> 00:14:06,910
Did you get the shot?
Did you?

241
00:14:07,420 --> 00:14:09,010
Wait, one more, one more!

242
00:14:09,560 --> 00:14:10,560
One more time.

243
00:14:10,880 --> 00:14:12,660
Okay, okay.

244
00:14:16,780 --> 00:14:18,249
- Are we ready?
- Yeah, almost.

245
00:14:18,250 --> 00:14:19,880
- String those together.
- Oh, okay.

246
00:14:26,540 --> 00:14:27,540
Grandpa.

247
00:14:30,730 --> 00:14:32,670
I've decided to move in with Wataru.

248
00:14:33,870 --> 00:14:34,870
Oh?

249
00:14:35,570 --> 00:14:36,930
Moving in together again?

250
00:14:37,770 --> 00:14:38,770
Yeah.

251
00:14:39,010 --> 00:14:40,650
Though it's a little different this time.

252
00:14:41,620 --> 00:14:42,620
I see.

253
00:14:44,480 --> 00:14:45,480
Yeah.

254
00:14:46,960 --> 00:14:49,080
The person I want to
photograph every day...

255
00:14:49,640 --> 00:14:50,640
is Wataru.

256
00:14:54,520 --> 00:14:55,520
Is that so?

257
00:14:56,590 --> 00:14:57,590
Yeah.

258
00:15:00,930 --> 00:15:02,010
To be honest,

259
00:15:02,570 --> 00:15:03,890
I don't really understand it all.

260
00:15:06,000 --> 00:15:07,000
I know.

261
00:15:08,590 --> 00:15:09,590
But,

262
00:15:10,400 --> 00:15:12,490
if he's someone you treasure, Minato,

263
00:15:13,380 --> 00:15:15,430
then I want to treasure him too.

264
00:15:17,930 --> 00:15:18,930
Thanks.

265
00:15:22,150 --> 00:15:23,150
Here.

266
00:15:28,930 --> 00:15:30,189
It's delicious!

267
00:15:30,190 --> 00:15:32,839
Gakudo, Wataru, let's take a photo.

268
00:15:32,840 --> 00:15:33,840
Smile for the camera!

269
00:15:35,950 --> 00:15:36,950
Me too.

270
00:15:38,010 --> 00:15:40,090
I treasure the person
you treasure too.

271
00:15:40,580 --> 00:15:41,580
Yeah.

272
00:15:41,780 --> 00:15:43,580
That would be your grandma.

273
00:15:45,350 --> 00:15:46,550
Wataru and I...

274
00:15:46,940 --> 00:15:48,140
are just like you and Grandma,

275
00:15:48,600 --> 00:15:49,700
aren't we?

276
00:15:53,090 --> 00:15:54,090
Maybe so.

277
00:15:55,350 --> 00:15:56,350
Yeah.

278
00:16:11,420 --> 00:16:12,620
Minato-kun~

279
00:16:13,850 --> 00:16:14,850
Hey.

280
00:16:14,990 --> 00:16:16,310
Are you really sure about Wataru?

281
00:16:16,600 --> 00:16:18,820
Is he really the only one for you?

282
00:16:19,140 --> 00:16:21,750
Yes. It has to be him.

283
00:16:22,190 --> 00:16:24,729
- Yay! You pass!
- How should I put it?

284
00:16:24,730 --> 00:16:27,250
I actually thought you passed
from the very beginning.

285
00:16:28,050 --> 00:16:31,190
- Stop it, what are you doing?
- It's fine, I'm just talking to Minato.

286
00:16:31,230 --> 00:16:32,930
No, no, no, let him go.

287
00:16:33,400 --> 00:16:34,800
Cut it out!

288
00:16:35,920 --> 00:16:36,920
Wataru!

289
00:16:37,470 --> 00:16:38,660
Popsicles!

290
00:16:38,760 --> 00:16:40,000
Oh, I want one.

291
00:16:40,170 --> 00:16:42,129
- Let's go, Minato.
- Wait, you're taking Minato too?

292
00:16:42,130 --> 00:16:43,450
Of course he's coming. Let's go.

293
00:16:45,630 --> 00:16:46,630
We're heading over.

294
00:16:48,640 --> 00:16:51,070
- Thanks again.
- Thank you.

295
00:16:54,618 --> 00:16:56,470
Raise your hand when you're done.

296
00:16:56,800 --> 00:16:57,800
Got it?

297
00:16:58,000 --> 00:16:58,950
Okay.

298
00:16:58,951 --> 00:17:00,820
Ready, set, go!

299
00:17:05,950 --> 00:17:07,020
Is this okay?

300
00:17:07,990 --> 00:17:08,990
I'm not losing today.

301
00:17:09,950 --> 00:17:12,130
- Okay.
- First place!

302
00:17:13,660 --> 00:17:15,260
Yes! You guys are too slow!

303
00:17:15,690 --> 00:17:16,690
No way.

304
00:17:16,810 --> 00:17:17,810
That's impossible.

305
00:17:58,400 --> 00:17:59,440
I'm home!

306
00:18:00,340 --> 00:18:01,340
Welcome back.

307
00:18:03,930 --> 00:18:05,970
Ugh, so heavy.

308
00:18:06,300 --> 00:18:08,810
Your parents really sent us a lot of stuff.

309
00:18:09,050 --> 00:18:11,240
I know, right? How much did they buy?

310
00:18:12,970 --> 00:18:14,540
This could last us a week.

311
00:18:14,810 --> 00:18:15,810
Definitely.

312
00:18:41,370 --> 00:18:42,510
I win again.

313
00:18:52,010 --> 00:18:54,960
I know they're my parents,
but what was with that attitude?

314
00:18:55,950 --> 00:18:58,770
It's not like we're getting married.

315
00:19:00,780 --> 00:19:01,780
Hmm?

316
00:19:02,100 --> 00:19:04,300
Don't you dare look like
you're actually considering it.

317
00:19:04,450 --> 00:19:06,209
- Wataru.
- Wait, don't rush into things.

318
00:19:06,210 --> 00:19:07,040
Have you learned nothing?

319
00:19:07,110 --> 00:19:08,750
I was always better at studying than you.

320
00:19:08,800 --> 00:19:10,320
Well, that's true.

321
00:19:10,500 --> 00:19:12,076
But we haven't even finished moving in yet.

322
00:19:12,100 --> 00:19:13,119
It's too soon.

323
00:19:13,120 --> 00:19:14,730
And why does this feel like déjà vu?

324
00:19:15,580 --> 00:19:16,580
Wataru.

325
00:19:17,200 --> 00:19:18,200
Marry me.

326
00:19:22,220 --> 00:19:24,040
That's exactly what I'm talking about!

327
00:19:25,580 --> 00:19:26,580
Yeah.

328
00:19:27,770 --> 00:19:28,770
Come here.

329
00:19:28,870 --> 00:19:30,079
No thanks.

330
00:19:30,080 --> 00:19:31,080
- Come on!
- I'm good!

331
00:19:31,180 --> 00:19:32,956
- The mood was so good just now.
- No, no, no.

332
00:19:32,980 --> 00:19:33,980
It's fine.

333
00:19:35,180 --> 00:19:36,180
Cut it out.

334
00:19:36,390 --> 00:19:37,700
Wait a second.

335
00:19:37,880 --> 00:19:38,880
Hey.

336
00:19:39,780 --> 00:19:40,780
Stop.

337
00:19:41,600 --> 00:19:42,680
I said I'm fine!

338
00:19:42,810 --> 00:19:44,209
Just stay over there.

339
00:19:44,210 --> 00:19:45,240
Then you come over here.

340
00:19:53,420 --> 00:19:54,476
(3698 days until he says "yes")
Next time,

341
00:19:54,500 --> 00:19:55,600
let's go take some photos.

342
00:19:59,310 --> 00:20:00,310
Okay.

343
00:20:01,800 --> 00:20:03,199
(3690 days until he says "yes")

344
00:20:03,200 --> 00:20:05,130
I love the photos Wataru takes.

345
00:20:05,154 --> 00:20:06,446
(3686 days until he says "yes")

346
00:20:06,470 --> 00:20:08,110
Oh man, I'm so happy.

347
00:20:10,100 --> 00:20:12,500
(3682 days until he says "yes")

348
00:20:14,000 --> 00:20:16,100
(3077 days until he says "yes")

349
00:20:16,170 --> 00:20:17,170
There's a bug over there.

350
00:20:17,200 --> 00:20:19,400
(2965 days until he says "yes")

351
00:20:20,240 --> 00:20:21,240
Wataru?

352
00:20:21,264 --> 00:20:22,964
(2957 days until he says "yes")

353
00:20:23,600 --> 00:20:25,300
(2945 days until he says "yes")

354
00:20:25,350 --> 00:20:26,690
If we live together, we can
see each other every day.

355
00:20:26,700 --> 00:20:28,500
(2908 days until he says "yes")

356
00:20:28,820 --> 00:20:29,820
No... this is terrible.

357
00:20:29,900 --> 00:20:32,200
(2697 days until he says "yes")

358
00:20:34,000 --> 00:20:36,000
(2289 days until he says "yes")

359
00:20:37,650 --> 00:20:39,170
(2266 days until he says "yes")
Minato.

360
00:20:40,380 --> 00:20:41,650
Thank you.

361
00:20:41,860 --> 00:20:43,420
(2250 days until he says "yes")
Thanks.

362
00:20:43,500 --> 00:20:44,500
In our 10th year, too,

363
00:20:45,570 --> 00:20:47,890
(2129 days until he says "yes")
I'll be right by your side.

364
00:20:48,860 --> 00:20:50,019
Please marry me.

365
00:20:50,020 --> 00:20:52,319
(1529 days until he says "yes")

366
00:20:52,320 --> 00:20:53,320
What was that?

367
00:20:55,000 --> 00:20:59,500
(1459 days until he says "yes")

368
00:20:59,850 --> 00:21:01,149
It's so cold.

369
00:21:01,150 --> 00:21:05,750
(1310 days until he says "yes")

370
00:21:05,760 --> 00:21:07,660
It's still freezing.

371
00:21:09,000 --> 00:21:14,000
(1309 days until he says "yes")

372
00:21:22,260 --> 00:21:23,260
Will you...

373
00:21:24,720 --> 00:21:26,520
(45 days until he says "yes")
move in with me?

374
00:21:28,000 --> 00:21:29,200
(37 days until he says "yes")

375
00:21:30,000 --> 00:21:34,100
(36 days until he says "yes")

376
00:21:34,130 --> 00:21:35,600
Because I love you, Minato.

377
00:21:36,910 --> 00:21:38,570
I love you too, so it's okay.

378
00:21:40,000 --> 00:21:41,600
(35 days until he says "yes")

379
00:21:43,500 --> 00:21:44,600
(29 days until he says "yes")

380
00:21:44,620 --> 00:21:46,000
- Oh, this is good.
- Right?

381
00:21:47,800 --> 00:21:49,300
(28 days until he says "yes")

382
00:21:50,500 --> 00:21:55,500
(26 days until he says "yes")

383
00:21:57,530 --> 00:21:58,640
I'm not leaving again.

384
00:21:58,740 --> 00:22:00,820
(25 days until he says "yes")
How can you be so sure?

385
00:22:02,000 --> 00:22:05,000
(21 days until he says "yes")

386
00:22:06,000 --> 00:22:08,999
(20 days until he says "yes")

387
00:22:09,000 --> 00:22:10,250
We're best friends.

388
00:22:14,500 --> 00:22:19,500
(17 days until he says "yes")

389
00:22:19,510 --> 00:22:20,709
For now,

390
00:22:20,710 --> 00:22:21,610
(15 days until he says "yes")

391
00:22:21,700 --> 00:22:22,700
let's not see each other.

392
00:22:27,500 --> 00:22:29,800
(6 days until he says "yes")

393
00:22:31,000 --> 00:22:34,500
(2 days until he says "yes")

394
00:22:35,500 --> 00:22:39,900
(1 day until he says "yes")

395
00:22:40,180 --> 00:22:41,180
Wataru.

396
00:22:41,200 --> 00:22:43,300
(0 days until he says "yes")

397
00:22:43,380 --> 00:22:44,380
Will you...

398
00:22:45,310 --> 00:22:46,310
move in with me?

399
00:22:48,220 --> 00:22:49,220
Yeah.

400
00:22:49,990 --> 00:22:50,990
I'd love to.

401
00:23:00,300 --> 00:23:01,530
(Teaser)
Welcome home.

402
00:23:03,260 --> 00:23:04,260
I'm home.

403
00:23:06,033 --> 00:23:06,773
Close your eyes!

404
00:23:06,970 --> 00:23:09,030
I want to be with you forever, Wataru.

405
00:23:09,800 --> 00:23:11,220
I'm telling you...

406
00:23:11,440 --> 00:23:12,440
What is it?

407
00:23:12,441 --> 00:23:14,521
I think I just fell in love
with you all over again.
